\title[]{Quasiconformal mappings that highly distort dimensions of many parallel lines}

\date{\today}
\begin{abstract}
We construct a quasiconformal mapping of ${\mathbb{R}}^n$, $n \geq 2$, that simultaneously distorts the Hausdorff dimension of a nearly maximal collection of parallel lines by a given amount. This answers a question of Balogh, Monti, and Tyson.
\end{abstract}

